cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with distance metric learning for object classification and few-shot object detection, which are both topics related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method that learns the embedding space and the multi-modal distribution of each training category, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and optimization algorithms. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with multi-modal data, which involves multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for the creation of a new benchmark, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category as well.
